## Plan:
1. Create interaction scheme between front, back and model parts
2. Choosing a language / framework for creating a backend: Node.js, Deno, .NET, PHP
3. Select a database: MySql, Oracle, MongoDB, Redis, NoSQL. As a result, I chose MongoDB Atlas (cloud solution)
4. Create schemes for MongoDB
5. Start develop back with Express + Node + Mongo
6. Create routes for model interaction
7. Create service for 2 way request sending
8. Create service for sending emails with ready photos to user
9. Install CORS and solve CORS Troubles
10. Set response statuses
11. Dockerize/containerize server
12. Deploy to VM
13. Documentation

